SIMPLE: elect
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elect
<hw>E*lect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>electus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>eligere</ets> to elect; <ets>e</ets>
out + <ets>legere</ets> to choose. See <er>Legend</er>, and cf.
<er>Elite</er>, <er>Eclectic</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Chosen; taken
by preference from among two or more.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Colors quaint
<xex>elect</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Chosen as the object of mercy or
divine favor; set apart to eternal life.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>elect</xex> angels.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>1 Tim. v. 21.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Chosen to an office, but not yet actually inducted
into it; <as>as, bishop <ex>elect</ex>; governor or mayor
<ex>elect</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elect</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Elect
<hw>E*lect"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One chosen or set
apart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Behold my servant, whom I uphold; mine <qex>elect</qex>, in whom
my soul delighteth.</q> <rj><qau>Is. xlii. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Those who are
chosen for salvation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shall not God avenge his won <qex>elect</qex>?</q> <rj><qau>Luke
xviii. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elect</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Elect
<hw>E*lect"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Elected</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Electing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pick out; to
select; to choose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The deputy <qex>elected</qex> by the Lord.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To select or take for an office; to select by vote;
<as>as, to <ex>elect</ex> a representative, a president, or a
governor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>To designate, choose, or select,
as an object of mercy or favor.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To choose; prefer; select. See
<er>Choose</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electant</ent>⟦br⟧
